Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel and thinly slice half the @Red Onion{1}. Quarter @Lemon{1}. Dice @Tomato{1} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Trim and dice @Mini Cucumber{1}.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, combine sliced onion, @Sugar{1/2%tsp}, juice from half the lemon, and a large pinch of @Salt{pinch}. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; microwave for ~{60%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

In a separate small #bowl{}, combine tomato, cucumber, @Dried Oregano{1/2%teaspoon}, and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

In a third small bowl, combine @Sour Cream{6%tablespoon}, yogurt, and @Garlic Powder{1/2%teaspoon}. Season with salt and pepper. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Open package of @Diced Chicken Thighs{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; season with @Shawarma Spice Blend{1/2%tablespoon}, remaining @Garlic Powder{1/2%teaspoon}, salt, and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert), you can get started on them now!

Wrap @Pita Bread{2} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{60%seconds}.

Serve pickled onion (draining first), tomato-cucumber salad, white sauce, chicken, pitas, and remaining lemon wedges family style so everyone can build their own plate.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.